            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20ever%20been%20in%20a%20pitched%20battle%3F%20Nehemiah%20was!%20As%20he%20neared%20the%20end%20of%20constructing%20the%20wall%2C%20he%20remained%20ever%20vigilant.%20%20He%20never%20took%20off%20his%20armor%20in%20the%20day%20of%20battle%20and%20kept%20his%20weapon%20with%20him%20at%20all%20times.%20Relaxation%20was%20not%20an%20option.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAt%20times%20the%20spiritual%20warfare%20in%20life%20can%20reach%20a%20fever%20pitch.%20Satan%20knows%20when%20you%20are%20approaching%20a%20breakthrough%20threshold%20in%20the%20advancement%20of%20the%20Kingdom%20of%20Christ.%20But%20just%20like%20a%20sports%20team%20that%20fights%20hardest%20in%20a%20goal-line%20stand%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20hold%20steady%20and%20remain%20firm%20in%20the%20fiercest%20moment%20of%20battle.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAs%20Paul%20said%2C%20%22Use%20every%20piece%20of%20God's%20armor%20to%20resist%20the%20enemy%20in%20the%20time%20of%20evil%2C%20so%20that%20after%20the%20battle%20you%20will%20still%20be%20standing%20firm%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(Ephesians%206%3A13).%20When%20you%20are%20facing%20a%20crisis%20and%20engaged%20in%20spiritual%20warfare%2C%20don't%20stop%20battling%20the%20devil%20until%20the%20breakthrough%20comes.%20There%20will%20be%20plenty%20of%20time%20for%20rest%20when%20the%20battle%20is%20won!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Nehemiah.3:15-5:13",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3ENehemiah%203%3A15-5%3A13%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_15%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Fountain%20Gate%20was%20repaired%20by%20Shallum%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A15a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Syriac%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EShallun.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Col-hozeh%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Mizpah%20district.%20He%20rebuilt%20it%2C%20roofed%20it%2C%20set%20up%20its%20doors%2C%20and%20installed%20its%20bolts%20and%20bars.%20Then%20he%20repaired%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20pool%20of%20Siloam%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A15b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Epool%20of%20Shelah%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20another%20name%20for%20the%20pool%20of%20Siloam.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20near%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20garden%2C%20and%20he%20rebuilt%20the%20wall%20as%20far%20as%20the%20stairs%20that%20descend%20from%20the%20City%20of%20David.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_16%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20to%20him%20was%20Nehemiah%20son%20of%20Azbuk%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20half%20the%20district%20of%20Beth-zur.%20He%20rebuilt%20the%20wall%20from%20a%20place%20across%20from%20the%20tombs%20of%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20family%20as%20far%20as%20the%20water%20reservoir%20and%20the%20House%20of%20the%20Warriors.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_17%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20to%20him%2C%20repairs%20were%20made%20by%20a%20group%20of%20Levites%20working%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20Rehum%20son%20of%20Bani.%20Then%20came%20Hashabiah%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20half%20the%20district%20of%20Keilah%2C%20who%20supervised%20the%20building%20of%20the%20wall%20on%20behalf%20of%20his%20own%20district.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_18%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20down%20the%20line%20were%20his%20countrymen%20led%20by%20Binnui%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20a%20few%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%2C%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%2C%20and%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%203%3A24%3B%2010%3A9)%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3EBavvai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Henadad%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20other%20half%20of%20the%20district%20of%20Keilah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_19%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20to%20them%2C%20Ezer%20son%20of%20Jeshua%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20Mizpah%2C%20repaired%20another%20section%20of%20wall%20across%20from%20the%20ascent%20to%20the%20armory%20near%20the%20angle%20in%20the%20wall.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_20%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20to%20him%20was%20Baruch%20son%20of%20Zabbai%2C%20who%20zealously%20repaired%20an%20additional%20section%20from%20the%20angle%20to%20the%20door%20of%20the%20house%20of%20Eliashib%20the%20high%20priest.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_21%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EMeremoth%20son%20of%20Uriah%20and%20grandson%20of%20Hakkoz%20rebuilt%20another%20section%20of%20the%20wall%20extending%20from%20the%20door%20of%20Eliashib%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_22%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20next%20repairs%20were%20made%20by%20the%20priests%20from%20the%20surrounding%20region.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_23%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20them%2C%20Benjamin%20and%20Hasshub%20repaired%20the%20section%20across%20from%20their%20house%2C%20and%20Azariah%20son%20of%20Maaseiah%20and%20grandson%20of%20Ananiah%20repaired%20the%20section%20across%20from%20his%20house.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_24%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20was%20Binnui%20son%20of%20Henadad%2C%20who%20rebuilt%20another%20section%20of%20the%20wall%20from%20Azariah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20to%20the%20angle%20and%20the%20corner.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_25%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EPalal%20son%20of%20Uzai%20carried%20on%20the%20work%20from%20a%20point%20opposite%20the%20angle%20and%20the%20tower%20that%20projects%20up%20from%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20upper%20house%20beside%20the%20court%20of%20the%20guard.%20Next%20to%20him%20were%20Pedaiah%20son%20of%20Parosh%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_26%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3Ewith%20the%20Temple%20servants%20living%20on%20the%20hill%20of%20Ophel%2C%20who%20repaired%20the%20wall%20as%20far%20as%20a%20point%20across%20from%20the%20Water%20Gate%20to%20the%20east%20and%20the%20projecting%20tower.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_27%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20came%20the%20people%20of%20Tekoa%2C%20who%20repaired%20another%20section%20across%20from%20the%20great%20projecting%20tower%20and%20over%20to%20the%20wall%20of%20Ophel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_28%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EAbove%20the%20Horse%20Gate%2C%20the%20priests%20repaired%20the%20wall.%20Each%20one%20repaired%20the%20section%20immediately%20across%20from%20his%20own%20house.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_29%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20Zadok%20son%20of%20Immer%20also%20rebuilt%20the%20wall%20across%20from%20his%20own%20house%2C%20and%20beyond%20him%20was%20Shemaiah%20son%20of%20Shecaniah%2C%20the%20gatekeeper%20of%20the%20East%20Gate.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_30%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20Hananiah%20son%20of%20Shelemiah%20and%20Hanun%2C%20the%20sixth%20son%20of%20Zalaph%2C%20repaired%20another%20section%2C%20while%20Meshullam%20son%20of%20Berekiah%20rebuilt%20the%20wall%20across%20from%20where%20he%20lived.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_31%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EMalkijah%2C%20one%20of%20the%20goldsmiths%2C%20repaired%20the%20wall%20as%20far%20as%20the%20housing%20for%20the%20Temple%20servants%20and%20merchants%2C%20across%20from%20the%20Inspection%20Gate.%20Then%20he%20continued%20as%20far%20as%20the%20upper%20room%20at%20the%20corner.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_3_32%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20other%20goldsmiths%20and%20merchants%20repaired%20the%20wall%20from%20that%20corner%20to%20the%20Sheep%20Gate.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_1%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ENehemiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EEnemies%20Oppose%20the%20Rebuilding%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Verses%204%3A1-6%20are%20numbered%203%3A33-38%20in%20Hebrew%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3ESanballat%20was%20very%20angry%20when%20he%20learned%20that%20we%20were%20rebuilding%20the%20wall.%20He%20flew%20into%20a%20rage%20and%20mocked%20the%20Jews%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_2%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3Esaying%20in%20front%20of%20his%20friends%20and%20the%20Samarian%20army%20officers%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20does%20this%20bunch%20of%20poor%2C%20feeble%20Jews%20think%20they%26%23x2019%3Bre%20doing%3F%20Do%20they%20think%20they%20can%20build%20the%20wall%20in%20a%20single%20day%20by%20just%20offering%20a%20few%20sacrifices%3F%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Do%20they%20actually%20think%20they%20can%20make%20something%20of%20stones%20from%20a%20rubbish%20heap%26%23x2014%3Band%20charred%20ones%20at%20that%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_3%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ETobiah%20the%20Ammonite%2C%20who%20was%20standing%20beside%20him%2C%20remarked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThat%20stone%20wall%20would%20collapse%20if%20even%20a%20fox%20walked%20along%20the%20top%20of%20it!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_4%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20I%20prayed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHear%20us%2C%20our%20God%2C%20for%20we%20are%20being%20mocked.%20May%20their%20scoffing%20fall%20back%20on%20their%20own%20heads%2C%20and%20may%20they%20themselves%20become%20captives%20in%20a%20foreign%20land!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_5%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EDo%20not%20ignore%20their%20guilt.%20Do%20not%20blot%20out%20their%20sins%2C%20for%20they%20have%20provoked%20you%20to%20anger%20here%20in%20front%20of%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Efor%20they%20have%20thrown%20insults%20in%20the%20face%20of.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20builders.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_6%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20last%20the%20wall%20was%20completed%20to%20half%20its%20height%20around%20the%20entire%20city%2C%20for%20the%20people%20had%20worked%20with%20enthusiasm.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_4_7%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Verses%204%3A7-23%20are%2